The paper deals with document listing, which is a fundamental problem in information retrieval and string algorithms. The focus is on repetitive collections, which are commonly studied in the context of compressed data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely categories. The paper also introduces new techniques for range data structures and grammar-based indexes, which are relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses the Lempel-Ziv parsing algorithm, which is a popular compression technique, and its application to document listing, which is relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
